1 cup flour
1/4 cup salt
2 T cream of tarter
1 cup water
2 tsp. food color
1 T. oil
In a bowl combine flour, salt, cream of tarter.  Set aside.
Combine water, food color oil in a pot, add dry ingredients to pot.
cook and stir 3 - 5 minutes until mixture forms a ball.
turn out onto lightly floured surface.
knead until smooth.
store in airtight container or plastic bag.
keeps in fridge up to 1 year.
Ida County's cooking up-cookbook
Mary Tyler recipe--1995
